This paper involves a real-world robotic manipulation task, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach based on deep neural networks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper involves modeling the dynamics of robot's interactions directly from images, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves multi-step decision making, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
